{
  "doc_id": "45247",
  "text": "All FjTOe plasmids carrying the S marker also conferred resistance to spectinomycin, an indication that the resistance was caused by an adenylylating enzyme [CITATION_1] . The streptomycin resistance coded for was low, the MIC of carrier strains being about 32 /tg/ml. The small independent SSu resistance plasmids did not code for spectinomycin resistance, an indication that the inactivation of the drug was caused by a phosphorylating enzyme. They conferred much higher streptomycin resistance, MIC 250 /ig/ml, on their carrier strains.",
